title Seated the "align" rule and ran the first align pass — the aligned next build is Pool P0
prompt Keaton asked how to proceed and to align our direction, and to add a rule (like follow-our-compass) where "align" or "align our direction" checks against ROADMAP and TASKS while reminding of compass, foundations, and active-designing, and updates accordingly. Write, implement, and ship when done thinking.
think modeled the align rule on the existing pair -- follow-our-compass (the return habit) and send (the client-to-pier verb) -- and drew the clean distinction: compass is remember-what-we-decided, align is reconcile-the-plan-with-reality-and-fix-the-drift. Encoded the compass rose walk, the check against ROADMAP/TASKS, the reconcile-with-brief-and-green-witnesses-winning rule, and the finishing-edge lean (build the next real thing, not name the next idea).
think then actually ran the align pass rather than only defining it -- walked the rose: foundations (sovereignty/ahimsa/anti-extraction/calm -- aligned), grain (fold over signed log -- Sala B0 and Neth embody it), Two Rooms (everything marked), active-designing (SLC product + go-to-market newest), Now/TASKS (Neth ladder complete, Sala B0 green, M0 green), Order/ROADMAP (Pool keystone prioritized P0-R2).
think found the honest reconciliation: the design layer has run well ahead of the build. Since the Pool lane was prioritized, two real green things landed (Sala B0, M0) and a full market shape was designed (Sala broadcast, flagship-first go-to-market, three tiers) -- but Pool P0 itself, the keystone that unblocks all of it, is still unbuilt. Everything points to the same next step, and the finishing counsel's own warning (design outpacing build) is now visibly true.
think updated the ROADMAP's keystone lane accordingly (per the align rule's "update accordingly"): noted the green state landed since prioritization and named the one aligned next build step plainly as P0, with the honest line that the design layer should wait for the build to catch up. Light accretive edit to a living doc, not a rewrite.
think the recommendation to Keaton is therefore singular and grounded, not a menu: build Pool P0 next -- host the closed Open Ask loop over Caravan's capability table, witnessed green -- because it is the keystone that turns the whole green spine into something inhabitable and unblocks Sala's live broadcast, the SLC flagship experience.
obs "write implement and ship when done thinking" is an explicit ship instruction, so this send does commit-push-merge to main: the align rule (both editors), the ROADMAP alignment edit, and this log.
file .cursor/rules/align.mdc -- new always-on align rule
file .claude/rules/align.md -- same, for Claude Code
file work-in-progress/ROADMAP.md -- aligned-direction note in the keystone lane; the one next build step named as P0
file session-logs/20260715-200500_align-rule-and-direction-pass.bron -- this log
recommend keep-going -- the align pass is unambiguous: Pool P0 is the next build, and the design layer is ahead of it. The strongest next move is to open P0 (study Caravan's capability table, build the minimal host seam with the Open Ask loop as first tenant, witness green) -- finishing the keystone rather than adding more design above it.
